.TH "RRIP_GUI" "1" "2026-06-10" "" "User Commands"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
rrip_gui - secure audio CD ripper, GTK3 graphical interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]rrip_gui\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]rrip_gui\f[R] is the GTK3 graphical interface of Rubyripper, a
secure audio CD ripper inspired by Exact Audio Copy (EAC).
It uses \f[B]cdparanoia\f[R](1) in a sophisticated way to ensure
accurate rips: each track is ripped multiple times and the results
compared chunk by chunk to detect and correct read errors.
.PP
On startup, \f[B]rrip_gui\f[R] automatically scans the CD drive and
fetches disc metadata from GnuDB or MusicBrainz (according to
preferences).
The main window presents five buttons in a left-side panel:
.TP
\f[B]Preferences\f[R]
Opens the preferences dialog with sections for Secure ripping, TOC
analysis, Codecs, Metadata, and Other settings.
These mirror the options available in the command-line interface
\f[B]rrip_cli\f[R](1).
.TP
\f[B]Scan drive\f[R]
Re-reads the disc currently in the drive and refreshes the track listing
and metadata.
.TP
\f[B]Open tray / Close tray\f[R]
Ejects or loads the disc drive.
.TP
\f[B]Rip cd now!\f[R]
Starts the ripping and encoding process using the current preferences
and track selection.
A progress view shows ripping and encoding progress along with the live
log output.
.TP
\f[B]Exit / Abort\f[R]
Exits the application, or aborts an ongoing rip when one is in progress.
.SS Preferences dialog
.PP
The preferences dialog provides the same configuration options as the
interactive menus in \f[B]rrip_cli\f[R](1):
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Secure ripping\f[R]: drive device, offset, padding, cdparanoia
parameters, chunk match counts, maximum attempts, ejection policy, log
policy.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]TOC analysis\f[R]: cuesheet, single-file image mode, hidden tracks,
pre-gap handling, pre-emphasis.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Codecs\f[R]: FLAC, Ogg Vorbis, MP3 (LAME), AAC (Nero or
Fraunhofer), WavPack, Opus, WAV, external encoder, playlist generation,
encoding threads, audio normalisation.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Metadata\f[R]: provider selection (GnuDB or MusicBrainz), server
settings, country and date preferences.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Other\f[R]: output directory, file naming schemes, log viewer, file
manager.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[B]$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/rubyripper/settings\f[R]
User configuration file (defaults to
\f[B]\[ti]/.config/rubyripper/settings\f[R] when
\f[B]XDG_CONFIG_HOME\f[R] is not set).
Created on first run and shared with \f[B]rrip_cli\f[R](1).
.TP
\f[B]\[ti]/.local/share/rubyripper/\f[R]
Local cache for GnuDB metadata entries.
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]rrip_cli\f[R](1), \f[B]cdparanoia\f[R](1), \f[B]flac\f[R](1),
\f[B]oggenc\f[R](1), \f[B]lame\f[R](1)
